Escalate privileges to Root - sudo su
Add a new group - groupadd (name)
verify new group - cat /etc/group
Add a new user - adduser (name), add password when prompted and fill other fields if necessary
Add a user to group - usermod -G (groupname) (username)
verify new users in the password file - cat /etc/passwd
view created users in shadow file - cat /etc/shadow
To identify open port - nmap localhost
To use administrative privileges with Nmap - sudo nmap –sU localhost
To perform a version detection to research vulnerability - nmap –sV localhost
To initiate a script scan and capture SSH keys - nmap –A localhost